Sentencas: Symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells (S-SOFCs) are prepared via a facile one-step co-sintering method with highly reactive Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (SDC) electrolyte and Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta (SFM) electrodes.
Titulo: Tailoring the electrolyte and cathode properties for optimizing the performance of symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by one-step co-sintering method

Sentencas: The phase compositions and microstructures are studied by XRD, TEM, and FESEM techniques, and the electrolyte-supported single cells with gas-tight SDC electrolyte and porous SFM-SDC electrode are prepared after one-step co-sintering at 1100 degrees C or higher temperatures for 4 h. In particular, the AC impedance spectra reveal that the SDC electrolyte sintered at 1200 degrees C exhibits the highest oxide ionic conductivity of similar to 35 mS/cm at 700 degrees C, while the electrode polarization resistance achieves the lowest value of 0.32 Omega.cm(2) at 700 degrees C in air for the sample co-sintered at 1100 degrees C. Accordingly, the output measurements are carried out on the single cells co-sintered at 1100 degrees C and 1200 degrees C.
Titulo: Tailoring the electrolyte and cathode properties for optimizing the performance of symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by one-step co-sintering method

Sentencas: It is found that the single cell co-sintered at 1200 degrees C possesses the highest peak power density of 216 mW/cm(2) at 700 degrees C, demonstrating the potential application of the one-step co-sintering method in low-cost manufacturing of S-SOFCs.
Titulo: Tailoring the electrolyte and cathode properties for optimizing the performance of symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells fabricated by one-step co-sintering method
